source_objects.title: Home Improvement & Gardening
source_objects.description: Discover new how-to projects and learn advice from other do-it-yourselfers to fix up your home.

items.title: The Basics of Household Wiring. The Electrical System A to Z
items.headline: Everything Electricity, from your Circuit (Breaker) Panel, Outlets, Switches, Receptacles, Light Fixtures, Cable, Wire..
objectives_summary: Understand how electricity works, how it is generated, transmitted to, and distributed throughout your home.
Wire a receptacle (regular, switched, GFCI), a single-pole switch (3 and 4-way), a light fixture, and more!
Have the knowledge and skills to safely and competently complete most home electrical projects and repairs.

items.title: Permaculture Design Course
items.headline: Learn to apply sustainable and productive land use design strategies to any property or site, anywhere in the world!
objectives_summary: You will gain an understanding of Permaculture theory.
You will learn to apply Permaculture design strategies to any site, anywhere in the world.
You will build your knowledge of all the necessary aspects (like growing food, enriching soils and using waste as a resource) to become fully conversant with Permaculture design.

items.title: Aquaponic Gardening: Growing Fish and Vegetables Together
items.headline: Grow an entire dinner right in your backyard with aquaponics! Safe, healthy fish and organic vegetables with no weeds!
objectives_summary: To teach new, inspired aquaponic gardeners in a way that is straightforward and unitimidating.

Increase Positive Energy within the Home or Business

items.title: Automate and Animate Your Holiday Lights Using RGB Pixels

objectives_summary: Select the minimum components necessary to assemble an RGB Pixel display.
Connect, load and configure the components in their display.
Create and play a sequence (lighting instructions) to animate patterns on the display.

items.headline: Learn where, when and what to plant in your backyard garden.
objectives_summary: Learn where, when and what to plant in your backyard garden!

By the end of the course, participants will learn strategies to create a sustainable farm

items.headline: Planning For The Build
objectives_summary: Taking this first of eight courses Will give you a full understand of what it takes to prepare for the build. From raw land through building design.

items.title: Aquaponics Farming & Gardening + Design Case Study
items.headline: Wether you're thinking of an aquaponics farm or garden this course teaches you the how to's of designing & building one.
objectives_summary: The course is designed for someone with or without the basic understanding of how aquaponics works and also for those who are looking to enhance their knowledge of the science, the operations and the design process of building an aquaponics farm, both backyard and small commercial scale. This course contains materials derived not only from the experience of running a small commercial farm but also from academic research on aquaponics conducted in the past two decades.
Aquaponics farming, hobby gardening and design

organic food production, growing organic food, growing without chemicals, gardening organically, grow food at home, soilless growing, making money with aquaponics, running operating an aquaponics farm, non chemical organic pest control, biological pest control, aquaculture design, aquaponics gardening, aquaponics profitability, fish and aquaponics, tilapia in aquaponics

items.title: Growing Mushrooms Indoors for Business and Pleasure
items.headline: Learn to grow Oyster and Lion's Mane Mushrooms in small spaces - for Beginner Home Growers and Farming Entrepreneurs
objectives_summary: How to grow Oyster and Lions Mane mushrooms indoors using basic equipment
What mushrooms are, what they need and how they grow
How to turn a liquid culture or spore syringe to mushrooms - through making grain spawn, colonising substrate and fruiting mushrooms

items.title: Beekeeping for Beginners: How to Be a Successful Beekeeper!

visible_instructors.title: Tonya Wells and Brianna Wells
visible_instructors.job_title: Owners / Beekeepers of Queen Bri's Honey in Oklahoma City

items.headline: Learning Everything You Need to Know to Become a Successful Beekeeper
objectives_summary: Students will learn about the history of beekeeping and collecting honey for food.
They will have a firm understanding about why honey bees are dying and how to help them.
Students will learn the cost/time commitment, equipment needed, and everything else they need to know to become a beekeeper.

items.headline: A-Z gardening instructions for creating a healthy and delicious edible garden in your own backyard, patio, or balcony.
objectives_summary: Grow delicious and healthy vegetables in any size garden.  Garden design, soil preparation, plant selection, pest and disease control, and harvesting are covered step by step and in detail.  Includes Master Gardener Tips useful for both beginning and more advanced gardeners.

items.title: Background to Beekeeping: Start with Why!
items.headline: Understand in depth why you should become a beekeeper and how beekeeping can transform your life for the better.
objectives_summary: Explain the surprising multiple benefits of beekeeping
Explain the history and current status of world bees and beekeeping
Explain the broad approaches to beekeeping
